WEBVTT

00:54.750 --> 00:58.166
<i>♪ Time breathed slower ♪</i>

00:58.250 --> 01:00.750
<i>♪ When we were younger ♪</i>

01:03.708 --> 01:07.916
<i>♪ And now it's racing so fast... ♪</i>

01:50.375 --> 01:51.791
What are you doing?

01:58.750 --> 01:59.833
Violet Markey?

02:02.375 --> 02:03.458
Oh, my God.

02:10.583 --> 02:11.583
Please go.

02:13.083 --> 02:15.250
- Well, I don't think that's very...
- Just go!

02:31.291 --> 02:32.625
What are you doing?

02:33.041 --> 02:34.166
I asked you first.

02:38.125 --> 02:39.666
This is higher than I thought.

02:44.666 --> 02:45.666
Hey.

02:46.708 --> 02:47.708
Hey, look.

02:48.625 --> 02:49.791
Look what I can do.

02:51.791 --> 02:53.541
Stop. Stop!

03:05.166 --> 03:06.166
Hey, Violet.

04:04.750 --> 04:07.875
Hey. Do you have plans this weekend?
My parents are gonna be out of town.

04:07.958 --> 04:10.375
I was thinking about having a party
or something.

04:16.541 --> 04:17.541
Violet?

04:18.791 --> 04:19.791
You OK?

04:23.833 --> 04:25.250
How's everything going?

04:26.208 --> 04:27.916
"Everything" is a really big word.

04:28.916 --> 04:31.375
- Let's start with...
- Do you mean physically?

04:31.458 --> 04:34.166
Emotionally?
Those both could encompass "everything."

04:34.250 --> 04:36.083
Or is "everything" encompassed
by both things?

04:36.166 --> 04:37.916
Are you feeling overwhelmed by anything?

04:38.000 --> 04:39.800
If "everything" is encompassed
by both things,

04:39.833 --> 04:42.153
are they a part of our reality,
or are they somewhere else?

04:42.208 --> 04:43.666
This isn't funny, Theodore.

04:45.416 --> 04:46.416
Finch.

04:47.625 --> 04:49.791
I need you
to take these meetings seriously.

04:49.875 --> 04:50.875
I get it.

04:51.583 --> 04:53.750
OK, do you "get"
that you're on probation,

04:54.791 --> 04:56.541
and in danger of not graduating?

04:58.750 --> 05:01.333
You've already missed
two weeks of school this year.

05:01.958 --> 05:03.000
Yeah, um...

05:04.416 --> 05:06.125
- my grandma...
- Stop one second.

05:06.208 --> 05:07.916
I just wanna clarify real quickly.

05:08.000 --> 05:11.125
Is this the grandma who's died four times
over the past three years?

05:12.000 --> 05:13.333
Five times, actually.

05:14.083 --> 05:15.166
This is the fifth.

05:18.625 --> 05:19.875
She's our miracle.

05:21.750 --> 05:25.000
I really wanna help you,
but you've gotta take this seriously.

05:26.291 --> 05:30.541
I mean, you agreed to these terms,
these weekly counseling sessions,

05:30.625 --> 05:33.375
maintaining a B-average,
extracurricular participation.

05:33.458 --> 05:35.500
And I am loving pottery.

05:36.125 --> 05:37.125
Come on, man.

05:37.583 --> 05:38.708
Look, I get it.

05:38.791 --> 05:40.916
If I screw anything up, I'm out.

05:41.666 --> 05:43.541
We're not askin' a lot of you, Finch.

05:45.083 --> 05:46.375
You just need to show up.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.480
My parents are pissed
because I missed early admissions,

05:50.541 --> 05:52.125
but it's not like that matters, anyway.

05:52.208 --> 05:54.125
I mean, I know I'm gonna get in.

05:56.333 --> 05:57.916
Did you apply anywhere yet?

05:59.208 --> 06:01.083
- Hey.
- Hi.

06:01.625 --> 06:03.875
So, you going to Amanda's party?

06:05.333 --> 06:06.375
It'll be fun.

06:07.125 --> 06:08.208
So I've heard.

06:08.625 --> 06:10.625
It couldn't hurt
to have a little fun, right?

06:11.208 --> 06:15.125
Yo, do you think it'd be weird
if I named my kid after a famous person?

06:15.208 --> 06:18.666
Like, if I named him Danny DeVito Donahue,

06:18.750 --> 06:21.416
do you...
do you think he'd be mad about it?

06:22.375 --> 06:23.875
Is "DeVito" the middle name?

06:24.458 --> 06:25.458
Yeah.

06:25.875 --> 06:27.875
Follow-up question:
how high are you right now?

06:29.500 --> 06:33.250
On the scale,
I'd probably say very... this way.

06:33.333 --> 06:35.208
- On the scale...
- Yeah?

06:37.083 --> 06:38.458
What are you looking at?

06:39.000 --> 06:42.250
Just admiring the social norms
of teenage angst.

06:42.833 --> 06:45.041
- Are you looking at Violet Markey?
- Yep.

06:46.250 --> 06:47.250
Her, um...

06:48.250 --> 06:49.458
her sister died, right?

06:50.458 --> 06:51.333
Yeah, dude.

06:51.416 --> 06:52.416
Hm.

06:53.083 --> 06:54.625
Why ask about her all of a sudden?

06:54.708 --> 06:56.267
I'm intrigued.
A guy can't be intrigued?

06:56.291 --> 06:59.541
Well, a guy can be intrigued.
You being intrigued is weird.

07:00.125 --> 07:03.083
- Definitely weird.
- No, I don't think it's weird.

07:03.166 --> 07:04.333
I wouldn't say "weird."

07:04.416 --> 07:06.500
Wait, if you don't think you're weird,
well...

07:07.875 --> 07:10.333
- Yeah, that's true. Very true.
- She has a point.

07:19.583 --> 07:22.458
- Your guidance counselor called.
- Embryo?

07:22.541 --> 07:23.541
What?

07:25.541 --> 07:29.458
His name's Embry. I call him Embryo.
It's the little things, Kate.

07:29.541 --> 07:31.625
Did you do something
I should be worried about?

07:31.708 --> 07:34.375
I'm genuinely offended
by that supposition.

07:34.916 --> 07:36.250
- Finch.
- No.

07:37.000 --> 07:38.500
It's fine. I'll deal with it.

07:38.583 --> 07:40.750
- I hate when you say that.
- Why?

07:40.833 --> 07:44.083
Because what you really mean is
that I'm gonna have to deal with it.

07:46.500 --> 07:47.708
Did you cut class again?

07:47.791 --> 07:49.375
No! For fuck's sake,

07:49.458 --> 07:52.208
just go hang out with Tina
or whatever it is you do.

07:52.291 --> 07:53.291
I'm fine.

07:54.083 --> 07:57.333
OK. I'm gonna be home late.
There's food in the fridge.

07:57.416 --> 07:59.125
- Mm-hmm.
- Real food, Finch.

07:59.833 --> 08:00.708
Where's Mom?

08:00.791 --> 08:03.041
She had to go to Chicago for business.
Remember?

08:03.125 --> 08:05.291
- Oh, yeah, right. Cool.
- Love you.

08:05.583 --> 08:06.583
Hey.

08:10.583 --> 08:11.833
- Love you.
- Love you.

08:13.541 --> 08:15.375
No more cheese, Finch!

08:28.208 --> 08:29.666
I'm gonna get the dessert.

08:35.625 --> 08:38.791
Your mother and I know
that today couldn't have been easy.

08:39.707 --> 08:41.832
And it wasn't easy for us either.

08:46.541 --> 08:48.958
If you need to talk about it...

08:51.625 --> 08:53.416
I thought this would be nice.

09:05.875 --> 09:07.625
I've been making it for 19 years.

11:11.958 --> 11:13.666
As some of you
will be graduating

11:13.750 --> 11:15.416
and leaving us at the end of the year,

11:15.500 --> 11:19.208
I feel an obligation to make sure
you see the wondrous sights of Indiana

11:19.291 --> 11:20.375
while you can.

11:20.458 --> 11:23.458
To wander them, if you will.

11:24.458 --> 11:28.791
For your class project, you must report
on two or more wonders of Indiana.

11:28.875 --> 11:30.500
You will write about them,

11:30.583 --> 11:33.750
explain their significance
to you and to Indiana,

11:33.833 --> 11:35.458
and why you chose to visit them.

11:36.125 --> 11:38.250
I want you to take time
on this assignment.

11:38.333 --> 11:39.500
Be thoughtful.

11:42.458 --> 11:43.458
OK.

11:44.958 --> 11:45.958
What just happened?

11:46.750 --> 11:47.958
That was so weird.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.521
- What?
- All right, settle.

11:49.583 --> 11:50.625
Violet, are you OK?

11:51.708 --> 11:54.541
All right, let's take our seats.
Let's focus up.

11:55.166 --> 11:56.916
If you're done, Mr. Finch?

11:57.000 --> 12:01.041
Yes, I am done, and can I just say you
are doing a fine job teaching this class.

12:01.125 --> 12:03.125
My young brain is plump with knowledge.

12:03.916 --> 12:06.208
- Thank you, Mr. Finch.
- You're welcome.

12:06.708 --> 12:08.166
As I was saying,

12:08.250 --> 12:11.958
you'll be taking photos,
doing some drawings, capturing detail.

12:12.041 --> 12:14.750
You will be doing this in teams of two.

12:16.041 --> 12:17.458
Can we choose our partners?

12:17.875 --> 12:19.000
Yes, Mr. Finch.

12:21.958 --> 12:22.958
Hey.

12:25.916 --> 12:26.916
So, um...

12:27.958 --> 12:31.500
do you think that there's such a thing
as a perfect day?

12:32.791 --> 12:34.875
I'm the last person you should be asking.

12:59.708 --> 13:01.375
<i>For my geography class,</i>

13:01.458 --> 13:05.125
this teacher wants us to do this project
with a partner,

13:05.208 --> 13:07.291
and I just don't wanna do it.

13:07.708 --> 13:10.125
Well, did you ask
for an alternate project?

13:10.875 --> 13:12.750
Yeah, he just... he wouldn't listen.

13:13.583 --> 13:15.303
Well, maybe it's time
to get back out there.

13:15.750 --> 13:17.333
That's the same thing he said.

13:19.958 --> 13:21.166
I know it's hard.

13:22.666 --> 13:25.333
- But you just don't go out anymore.
- That's not true.

13:25.416 --> 13:27.791
When's the last time you hung out
with your friends?

13:29.250 --> 13:32.583
I think it would be really good
if you'd spend some time with them.

13:34.166 --> 13:37.625
So, if I hung out with my friends,
you'd get me outta this assignment?

13:41.333 --> 13:44.416
<i>♪ Speedy, speedy, slow down time
Gas station is running dry ♪</i>

13:44.500 --> 13:47.166
<i>♪ Mm-hmm, eh eh, mm-hmm ♪</i>

13:48.458 --> 13:52.375
<i>♪ Sweaty, sweaty, wonder why
Now it's always summer time ♪</i>

13:52.458 --> 13:53.458
Violet!

13:55.791 --> 13:58.083
- You came.
- I did.

13:58.833 --> 14:00.000
- Hey.
- Hi.

14:00.416 --> 14:03.166
- I'm gonna get a drink. Do you want one?
- I'm good.

14:03.250 --> 14:04.625
Come on, babe.

14:05.166 --> 14:06.166
OK.

14:47.041 --> 14:47.875
Yeah...

14:58.416 --> 14:59.500
Hey.

15:01.125 --> 15:02.458
That's a heavy pour.

15:03.083 --> 15:04.708
You know me. I love to rage.

15:04.791 --> 15:07.875
So, you wanna go out back?
Talk a little?

15:10.291 --> 15:12.708
I think I'm gonna leave pretty soon,
actually.

15:13.375 --> 15:16.125
Really? But... I mean, I just got here.

15:17.458 --> 15:19.500
It's just all a little much, you know?

15:21.208 --> 15:23.458
How much longer
are you gonna act like this?

15:25.125 --> 15:27.625
It's been months.
When are you gonna just...

15:32.750 --> 15:33.750
Nice.

15:35.666 --> 15:38.416
Violet, you know
I didn't mean it like that. Just...

15:57.708 --> 16:01.416
<i>Violet Markey,
if you're seeing this, you're still alive.</i>

16:01.500 --> 16:02.708
<i>Please call to confirm.</i>

16:03.166 --> 16:05.791
<i>765-276-8504.</i>

16:06.666 --> 16:10.958
<i>♪ I met you standin' on a ledge ♪</i>

16:11.041 --> 16:14.333
<i>♪ What's going on
Inside that pretty head?</i> ♪

16:14.791 --> 16:18.833
<i>♪ I met you standing on a ledge ♪</i>

16:18.916 --> 16:23.541
<i>♪ Why don't you come talk to me instead? ♪</i>

16:31.708 --> 16:32.833
Theodore Finch speaking.

16:32.916 --> 16:34.166
Take it down now.

16:36.708 --> 16:41.000
The video will self-destruct
in three, two...

16:42.291 --> 16:43.291
<i>...please refresh.</i>

16:46.541 --> 16:47.708
Why would you do that?

16:48.125 --> 16:49.750
I wanna talk about the bridge.

16:53.291 --> 16:57.208
<i>"I feel we can't go through
another of those terrible times."</i>

17:00.416 --> 17:03.166
One morning barely qualifies
as a terrible time.

17:03.541 --> 17:04.833
It's a quote.

17:05.750 --> 17:06.833
Virginia Woolf.

17:08.790 --> 17:09.790
OK.

17:11.208 --> 17:12.208
Can I come over?

17:13.333 --> 17:14.333
<i>Now?</i>

17:15.290 --> 17:16.375
Yeah.

17:26.500 --> 17:28.375
So...

17:29.333 --> 17:31.000
I Googled you.

17:33.958 --> 17:35.333
You <i>Googled </i> me?

17:37.750 --> 17:39.625
Yeah, what's with that...

17:40.250 --> 17:43.125
the website that you have
with your sister?

17:44.958 --> 17:45.958
Had.

17:50.458 --> 17:52.541
I read some of your stuff.
It's really good.

17:53.875 --> 17:55.125
I don't write anymore.

17:58.583 --> 18:01.791
So, you moved here from California.

18:04.333 --> 18:05.333
How was that?

18:06.666 --> 18:08.166
California to Indiana?

18:09.125 --> 18:10.416
Must've been different.

18:12.125 --> 18:13.125
Yeah.

18:23.375 --> 18:25.125
I didn't know that it happened there.

18:26.500 --> 18:27.750
At the bridge.

18:31.083 --> 18:32.708
I'm not, you know...

18:35.583 --> 18:36.916
Suicidal?

18:37.791 --> 18:38.791
You can say it.

18:39.500 --> 18:40.500
Well, I'm not.

18:42.458 --> 18:45.208
Whatever you are, I saved your life.

18:48.083 --> 18:49.250
No, you didn't.

18:50.666 --> 18:52.833
You're making a big deal out of nothing.

18:53.416 --> 18:55.625
Mm... kinda looked like somethin'.

18:58.250 --> 18:59.708
What do you want from me?

19:00.875 --> 19:03.875
I was just thinkin' that
we should be partners.

19:04.583 --> 19:06.041
For the wandering project.

19:06.750 --> 19:09.083
I think it would be good for you
to get out.

19:10.125 --> 19:11.541
Maybe I don't wanna get out.

19:12.625 --> 19:14.125
Maybe I'm sick of people.

19:17.041 --> 19:18.583
Yeah, people are stupid.

19:19.416 --> 19:24.416
But the tiniest few
might actually mean well.

19:26.083 --> 19:28.375
Why do you wanna do this with me, anyway?

19:29.833 --> 19:32.625
Because there are places
that need to be seen.

19:33.333 --> 19:35.583
Maybe even the smallest of places

19:36.250 --> 19:37.750
can mean something.

19:37.875 --> 19:39.291
At the very least,

19:40.041 --> 19:42.166
maybe they can mean something to us.

19:42.250 --> 19:43.333
Not an "us."

19:44.666 --> 19:48.625
Maybe they can mean something
to you and me.

19:48.708 --> 19:51.166
Jesus, they call <i>me </i> anti-social.

19:51.708 --> 19:54.291
Two wanders. That's all.

19:55.583 --> 19:57.583
We can do more if you end up loving it.

19:57.666 --> 19:58.666
I won't.

19:59.666 --> 20:00.750
You might.

20:01.375 --> 20:03.541
No, I won't.

20:07.583 --> 20:10.875
Oh, I found another quote for you.

20:14.083 --> 20:17.291
"I feel a thousand capacities
spring up in me."

20:18.458 --> 20:21.750
<i>The Waves. </i> It's from <i>The Waves.</i>

20:23.083 --> 20:26.708
You've got at least
a thousand capacities in you.

20:28.625 --> 20:30.083
Even if you don't think so.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.250
You can keep that one.

20:44.875 --> 20:47.250
You know people call you
"The Freak," right?

20:49.291 --> 20:50.291
Yeah.

20:51.416 --> 20:55.916
Sometimes I say and do things
without thinking, and...

20:57.041 --> 21:00.083
people don't like that,
people like labels.

21:00.166 --> 21:01.583
They like putting you in a box.

21:01.666 --> 21:04.291
They want you to be
who they want you to be.

21:07.666 --> 21:09.250
People don't like messy.

21:10.583 --> 21:11.583
Or different.

21:16.333 --> 21:19.208
My parents are calling Hudson
to get me outta the project,

21:19.291 --> 21:21.166
so you need to find another partner.

21:24.416 --> 21:25.416
OK.

21:29.625 --> 21:32.208
Good night, Violet Markey.

21:33.291 --> 21:34.291
Good night...

21:36.041 --> 21:37.333
Theodore Finch.

22:04.125 --> 22:05.875
Hey. Hey!

22:06.416 --> 22:07.416
Violet.

22:08.958 --> 22:10.125
Hey, where you going?

22:11.083 --> 22:12.083
Home.

22:12.708 --> 22:14.083
How'd it go with Hudson?

22:15.833 --> 22:16.833
Not great.

22:17.458 --> 22:18.458
Yeah.

22:19.000 --> 22:21.541
He feels pretty strongly
about participation.

22:28.416 --> 22:29.416
OK...

22:32.166 --> 22:33.541
but no cars.

22:34.958 --> 22:36.125
Come again?

22:36.208 --> 22:37.583
If you wanna do this with me,

22:37.666 --> 22:40.958
you have to figure out another way
because I'm not getting in a car.

23:09.041 --> 23:10.500
<i>Can I ask you a question?</i>

23:11.791 --> 23:14.000
<i>Where would you go
if you could go anywhere?</i>

23:15.916 --> 23:19.041
- <i>California.
- But you've already been there.</i>

23:20.791 --> 23:21.791
<i>Yeah.</i>

23:22.416 --> 23:24.791
<i>It's warm and it never snows.</i>

23:26.791 --> 23:30.000
<i>Don't you wanna know where I'd go
if I could go anywhere?</i>

23:31.333 --> 23:34.083
<i>Where would you go
if you could go anywhere?</i>

23:34.791 --> 23:38.333
<i>I'd go to a place
no one's ever been before.</i>

23:38.958 --> 23:40.208
<i>Undiscovered.</i>

23:40.291 --> 23:41.291
<i>Untouched.</i>

23:42.375 --> 23:44.583
<i>You could come... if you want.</i>

23:56.500 --> 23:57.541
That's it?

24:04.083 --> 24:05.583
Get on up here, Ultraviolet.

24:05.666 --> 24:06.666
No.

24:06.958 --> 24:08.125
Come on.

24:09.125 --> 24:10.958
Come on. The view is incredible.

24:15.333 --> 24:16.333
Come on.

24:28.541 --> 24:30.833
So, what do we think?

24:31.666 --> 24:33.500
The highest point in Indiana.

24:35.583 --> 24:39.666
I think if I were here for literally any
other reason than why you and I are here,

24:39.750 --> 24:40.833
I'd be pissed.

24:42.166 --> 24:45.083
Oh, wow. Is that a sense of humor
you're hiding in there?

24:45.166 --> 24:46.375
Hm.

24:48.833 --> 24:51.750
This is the lamest thing
I think I've ever seen.

25:03.708 --> 25:06.750
It's OK, you know?
You're not going to hell for laughing.

25:10.000 --> 25:12.041
It's pretty lame.

25:16.791 --> 25:18.416
It was my sister's birthday.

25:21.333 --> 25:22.791
She would've been 19.

25:25.291 --> 25:26.958
That's why I was at the bridge.

25:33.791 --> 25:34.958
Why were you there?

25:38.750 --> 25:39.916
I like to run.

25:43.083 --> 25:44.833
It's pretty early to run.

25:44.916 --> 25:45.916
Yeah.

25:50.916 --> 25:51.916
Let's jump.

25:54.333 --> 25:55.333
You with me?

25:59.291 --> 26:00.458
All right, on three.

26:02.041 --> 26:03.125
You gotta get ready.

26:03.208 --> 26:04.583
One... there it is,

26:04.666 --> 26:05.666
two,

26:06.416 --> 26:07.416
three.

26:10.708 --> 26:11.875
Wow.

26:12.500 --> 26:13.500
All right.

26:15.625 --> 26:18.125
These are the things we leave behind.

26:18.875 --> 26:19.875
Pick one.

26:22.916 --> 26:24.083
Not that one.

26:25.500 --> 26:26.958
Yeah. That's a good choice.

26:43.166 --> 26:45.166
- What?
- You didn't know?

26:46.000 --> 26:48.083
This is a motherfucking staring contest.

26:49.416 --> 26:50.583
You can't be serious.

26:51.000 --> 26:52.833
Look at my face. I'm really serious.

26:54.791 --> 26:55.791
Fine.

26:56.708 --> 26:58.000
I'm very competitive.

26:58.083 --> 26:59.083
Me too.

27:45.333 --> 27:47.083
I'm staying over at Tina's tonight.

27:48.291 --> 27:49.291
OK.

27:50.958 --> 27:51.958
"OK"?

27:53.208 --> 27:54.208
Yeah.

27:56.500 --> 27:58.125
Usually, that incites a diatribe

27:58.208 --> 28:00.708
- about how Tina's an asshole...
- "Diatribe." Good word.

28:00.791 --> 28:02.833
...and how I shouldn't spend
so much time with her.

28:04.000 --> 28:07.083
Yeah, well, it appears that
my many rantings on this topic

28:07.166 --> 28:10.083
have stuck with you,
and I don't have to preach anymore.

28:10.791 --> 28:12.041
What's going on with you?

28:13.875 --> 28:14.875
Nothing.

28:16.250 --> 28:17.375
You seem, like...

28:18.833 --> 28:19.833
goofy.

