29:27.166 --> 29:28.500
<i>than men are to women?"</i>

29:43.208 --> 29:47.083
<i>"My own brain is, to me,
the most unaccountable of machinery,</i>

29:47.166 --> 29:50.916
<i>always buzzing, humming,
soaring, roaring, diving,</i>

29:51.000 --> 29:52.333
<i>and then buried in mud.</i>

29:53.083 --> 29:54.250
<i>And why?</i>

29:54.333 --> 29:55.958
<i>What's this passion for?"</i>

30:08.625 --> 30:11.291
<i>"If you do not tell the truth
about yourself,</i>

30:11.625 --> 30:14.166
<i>you cannot tell it about other people."</i>

33:34.083 --> 33:35.583
Tell me about Eleanor.

33:42.500 --> 33:44.833
She was bossy... like you.

33:47.125 --> 33:48.333
I like her already.

33:52.250 --> 33:53.708
She hated reading.

33:56.666 --> 33:58.625
She only liked this Italian poet,

33:59.875 --> 34:01.333
Cesare Pavese.

34:02.583 --> 34:07.166
He said, "We do not remember days,
we remember moments."

34:10.250 --> 34:12.041
Any time I was having a bad day,

34:13.583 --> 34:15.208
she always said that.

34:15.291 --> 34:17.500
Like it was supposed to fix something.

34:18.625 --> 34:19.625
Did it?

34:21.750 --> 34:22.750
Yeah.

34:23.666 --> 34:24.666
It did.

34:27.666 --> 34:28.666
What else?

34:34.291 --> 34:35.750
She was my best friend.

34:42.083 --> 34:43.375
"Eleanor Markey.

34:44.625 --> 34:45.708
Sister...

34:47.250 --> 34:48.250
best friend."

34:52.250 --> 34:53.625
That's a pretty good epitaph.

34:57.625 --> 34:58.750
What would yours be?

35:02.958 --> 35:04.166
"Violet Markey.

35:06.583 --> 35:07.583
I was here."

35:11.916 --> 35:14.708
Yeah, I'm gonna have to steal that one
from you.

35:23.625 --> 35:25.000
You making pancakes?

35:25.791 --> 35:26.916
Yeah.

35:27.000 --> 35:28.708
- Blueberry pancakes?
- Yup.

35:30.583 --> 35:31.875
Lookin' pretty good.

35:33.500 --> 35:35.392
- Wanna flip 'em?
- Yeah, are they ready?

35:35.416 --> 35:37.708
- Yeah. Well, give it a...
- Almost ready.

35:38.750 --> 35:40.458
- These look pretty good.
- Yeah.

35:42.333 --> 35:43.333
OK.

35:44.666 --> 35:46.892
There we go. That one's good.

35:46.916 --> 35:49.197
Yeah, there you go. Golden brown

35:56.583 --> 35:58.375
- Hey.
- Hi.

35:58.458 --> 35:59.833
Where've you been?

36:00.708 --> 36:03.375
You're not mad that
I'm doing that project with Roamer, right?

36:03.833 --> 36:04.666
No.

36:04.750 --> 36:06.875
OK, cool.
'Cause it's, like, it's not a thing.

36:06.958 --> 36:09.083
No, it's fine. I'm doing it with Finch.

36:09.625 --> 36:10.625
With Finch?

36:11.000 --> 36:12.000
Yeah.

36:13.708 --> 36:16.625
You know that he's, like, kinda dangerous?

36:17.708 --> 36:18.916
No, he's not.

36:20.083 --> 36:22.541
He freaked out last year
and threw a chair at Roamer,

36:22.625 --> 36:24.375
like, in the middle of class.

36:25.666 --> 36:26.666
He did?

36:27.583 --> 36:31.416
Yeah, like, Roamer was fine,
but he's seriously fucked up.

36:43.958 --> 36:49.750
So, I was thinking we should check out
the Shoe Tree or the abandoned drive-in,

36:49.833 --> 36:52.125
depending on whatever you're feeling.

36:54.125 --> 36:55.291
What is this?

36:55.708 --> 36:57.916
That's a reminder that sooner or later,

36:58.291 --> 37:00.691
you're gonna have to get back
into the world all by yourself.

37:01.083 --> 37:02.875
But I'm happy pushing you for now.

37:04.958 --> 37:08.041
Well, I said
I was only gonna do two, so...

37:12.166 --> 37:14.083
I prefer Private Violet to...

37:14.875 --> 37:15.875
Public Violet.

37:15.958 --> 37:17.250
Can you put her on?

37:17.333 --> 37:18.333
I'll wait.

37:18.500 --> 37:20.333
Maybe you should
give her some space.

37:22.625 --> 37:25.125
Nice sweater. What's that, a cotton blend?

37:26.875 --> 37:30.458
People think this whole "freak" thing
is an act. I know it's real.

37:33.958 --> 37:35.000
Of course it is.

37:42.166 --> 37:43.208
How are things?

37:44.041 --> 37:46.625
Just your average teenage melodrama.

37:47.625 --> 37:49.708
Come on. You gotta give me more than that.

37:51.750 --> 37:53.875
People are always telling me what I am.

37:54.458 --> 37:55.458
A freak.

37:56.375 --> 37:57.375
I get it.

37:58.000 --> 38:00.333
Doesn't mean
it doesn't piss me off sometimes.

38:00.416 --> 38:02.250
Well, that must be hard.

38:08.916 --> 38:09.916
Come on, man.

38:10.458 --> 38:12.458
Come on. Help me out here.
Come on. Help me out.

38:18.583 --> 38:20.458
Maybe if...

38:21.333 --> 38:22.958
you got a fainting couch,

38:23.916 --> 38:25.625
you could put it right over there.

38:25.708 --> 38:28.625
It would really give me the <i>mise en scène</i>
that I was looking for.

38:29.291 --> 38:30.625
Tie the whole room together.

38:30.708 --> 38:33.250
Did you look into that support group
I told you to check out?

38:33.333 --> 38:35.708
I might've lost the info on that one.

38:35.791 --> 38:38.208
Come on, Theodore. It's a small ask, man.

38:39.291 --> 38:43.666
All right. It's Mondays
after school at First Congregational.

38:44.125 --> 38:46.416
- It's called Fresh Approach...
- Ooh!

38:46.500 --> 38:48.041
...and it is confidential,

38:48.458 --> 38:52.291
so you can say whatever you want
about anything that's bothering you.

38:53.250 --> 38:56.875
It is a safe space, Finch.

38:57.333 --> 38:58.833
I want you to think about it.

39:05.166 --> 39:07.000
What now? Now what are we doing? What?

39:07.083 --> 39:08.375
What's happenin'?

39:08.458 --> 39:09.500
Is this a knock-off?

39:09.583 --> 39:10.916
The Post-it?

39:11.541 --> 39:13.625
- This is off-brand.
- Please leave now.

39:29.125 --> 39:31.000
♪ <i>Hey, heart, on the road again ♪</i>

39:31.666 --> 39:33.500
<i>♪ Movin' on</i> ♪

39:34.416 --> 39:35.500
<i>♪ Forward ♪</i>

39:36.333 --> 39:38.791
<i>♪ Sticks and stones won't break bones ♪</i>

39:38.875 --> 39:42.458
<i>♪ We're in the car on the highway ♪</i>

39:43.666 --> 39:47.875
<i>♪ It's a magical feeling
That no one's got a hold ♪</i>

39:51.250 --> 39:54.625
<i>♪ You're a catalyst
To your own happiness you know... ♪</i>

39:54.708 --> 39:56.250
What are you looking at?

39:59.000 --> 40:00.541
There's a kid on my lawn.

40:04.583 --> 40:08.125
<i>♪ And it's your heart, it's alive ♪</i>

40:08.208 --> 40:10.333
<i>♪ It's pumping blood ♪</i>

40:11.041 --> 40:13.541
<i>♪ And the whole wide world is whistling ♪</i>

40:20.541 --> 40:23.541
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪</i>

40:26.875 --> 40:28.041
Wake up.

40:31.125 --> 40:32.125
Hey.

40:32.833 --> 40:34.250
Did you sleep out here?

40:35.750 --> 40:36.750
Yeah.

40:40.458 --> 40:43.250
I know you said that you were done,

40:43.875 --> 40:45.916
but what if I told you

40:46.000 --> 40:49.041
that I found the best wander
in the state of Indiana,

40:49.125 --> 40:51.208
possibly the world, but...

40:53.125 --> 40:54.500
it was 160 miles away?

40:55.375 --> 40:58.291
I'd say have fun,
and I can't wait to hear all about it.

40:58.833 --> 41:01.750
Come on! Just give it a chance.

41:01.833 --> 41:03.791
- At least sit inside.
- No, Finch.

41:03.875 --> 41:05.208
I'm not getting in a car!

41:05.291 --> 41:07.291
Look, here. I'll take the keys, and...

41:10.666 --> 41:14.083
I swear not to drive faster
than 30 miles per hour through town

41:14.166 --> 41:15.666
or 50 on the interstate.

41:16.625 --> 41:18.833
If at any time you wanna stop, we stop.

41:19.666 --> 41:21.625
You can't keep pushing people.

41:21.708 --> 41:25.833
You don't listen. We did it.
The project is over. This is over.

41:26.291 --> 41:28.791
You know this isn't
about a class assignment.

41:29.541 --> 41:33.208
This is about you being holed up
in your room or on your stupid bike,

41:33.291 --> 41:35.416
always circling
the same three-mile radius.

41:35.500 --> 41:38.416
And God forbid anyone risk upsetting
"Poor Violet," but...

41:39.500 --> 41:40.780
they're wrong.

41:42.500 --> 41:43.500
Violet.

41:43.916 --> 41:45.250
Is everything OK out here?

41:45.333 --> 41:46.666
- Fine.
- Hey.

41:46.750 --> 41:51.041
Sorry. Hey. Hi, I'm Theodore Finch.
Pleasure to meet you both.

41:51.125 --> 41:54.500
- Little early, don't you think, Theodore?
- Yes. Yes, it is early.

41:54.583 --> 41:56.000
That is a fair observation.

41:56.083 --> 41:58.916
But you see, I'm your daughter's partner
for the school project,

41:59.000 --> 42:01.375
and we really need to get to this place.

42:03.291 --> 42:05.416
Basically, I need her to get into the car.

42:05.500 --> 42:06.625
That car.

42:07.625 --> 42:10.208
That is extremely safe, insured,

42:10.791 --> 42:14.208
with an experienced driver who hasn't
gotten so much as a speeding ticket.

42:14.291 --> 42:15.708
This is for a school project?

42:16.125 --> 42:17.958
Yes, sir. We're partners.

42:19.958 --> 42:23.583
Well, Theodore, I think
it's Violet's decision to make, but...

42:25.083 --> 42:26.583
maybe not a bad idea.

42:39.666 --> 42:41.375
You think she's coming back?

42:41.458 --> 42:44.083
Hey, your guess is as good as ours.

42:55.500 --> 42:56.500
Oh.

42:57.291 --> 42:58.541
No, wait. No.

43:02.250 --> 43:05.708
OK. If I were keys, where would I hide?

43:15.375 --> 43:16.833
How are we doin' over there?

43:16.916 --> 43:17.916
Fine.

43:18.416 --> 43:19.333
You sure?

43:19.416 --> 43:21.750
Just stop asking me.
You're making it worse.

43:22.541 --> 43:23.958
Talk about something else.

43:24.791 --> 43:26.875
Usually, that is my forte.

43:26.958 --> 43:29.125
But right now, I got nothin'.

43:33.083 --> 43:35.541
♪ <i>...build this thing together ♪</i>

43:49.916 --> 43:51.166
It's a good song.

44:43.500 --> 44:46.083
I don't remember how fast we were going.

44:46.375 --> 44:48.250
It didn't seem fast.

44:55.666 --> 44:57.083
Then we were sliding...

45:03.708 --> 45:06.291
and Eleanor was saying, "I can't hold on."

45:10.666 --> 45:13.291
And then the car slammed into the bridge.

45:24.208 --> 45:25.541
I just remember the...

45:25.625 --> 45:27.625
the glass hitting my face

45:28.250 --> 45:29.750
and Eleanor screaming.

45:35.416 --> 45:36.416
Then...

45:37.375 --> 45:39.500
after that, it just all goes blank.

45:47.250 --> 45:49.166
When I woke up in the hospital,

45:51.333 --> 45:53.250
my mom told me she was gone.

46:00.958 --> 46:02.291
And that was it.

47:19.708 --> 47:21.291
Still mad you got in the car?

47:40.458 --> 47:42.875
- You really built this yourself?
- Yes, I did.

47:42.958 --> 47:43.958
That's impressive.

47:44.291 --> 47:46.791
- All right. Here we go.
- Let's do it.

47:46.958 --> 47:49.833
I'm gonna do it.

47:49.916 --> 47:51.556
Have a good one.

47:57.250 --> 47:58.833
I can see my house from here.

48:07.458 --> 48:08.458
Ah...

48:14.666 --> 48:17.541
Woo!

48:17.625 --> 48:18.625
Yeah!

48:19.041 --> 48:21.416
- That was amazing.
- Good job!

48:22.791 --> 48:24.125
Did it feel fast?

48:24.208 --> 48:27.416
Oh, yeah. It's just like the real thing.

48:27.750 --> 48:28.750
Are you ready?

48:30.125 --> 48:32.250
All right. Here we go. You ready?

48:32.333 --> 48:33.375
Oh, my God.

48:50.750 --> 48:52.375
Yes!

49:01.208 --> 49:02.750
Yeah!

49:02.833 --> 49:04.208
Yay!

49:05.875 --> 49:07.375
Oh, my God!

49:10.416 --> 49:11.833
I wanna go again.

49:12.875 --> 49:15.291
Ah!

49:33.958 --> 49:37.583
♪ <i>When I was just a kid they said ♪</i>

49:38.458 --> 49:41.708
<i>♪ "Kid, don't you cry" ♪</i>

49:42.625 --> 49:47.000
<i>♪ I am older now, I say ♪</i>

49:47.666 --> 49:50.458
<i>♪ "It's all right" ♪</i>

49:51.458 --> 49:55.583
<i>♪ Every tear rolling down is a... ♪</i>

49:56.416 --> 49:58.416
<i>♪ Lesson learned ♪</i>

50:00.166 --> 50:03.291
<i>♪ Are you too old to turn? ♪</i>

50:03.375 --> 50:07.875
<i>♪ Are you too young to burn? ♪</i>

50:07.958 --> 50:10.875
<i>♪ Too young ♪</i>

50:12.625 --> 50:17.083
♪ <i>Too young to burn...</i> ♪

50:17.833 --> 50:20.041
I got you somethin'. It's in the door.

50:24.291 --> 50:27.458
That, Ultraviolet, is a special place

50:27.541 --> 50:29.291
that I'm gonna take you to one day.

50:30.791 --> 50:31.791
Oh, yeah?

50:32.541 --> 50:35.833
Yeah, but you're gonna need
to start pullin' your weight, OK?

50:35.916 --> 50:36.958
I got you this...

50:37.541 --> 50:40.416
just in case you've forgotten
this is a school project,

50:41.083 --> 50:42.458
you have to write about it.

50:43.250 --> 50:44.291
Just me?

50:44.750 --> 50:45.916
You're the writer.

50:53.166 --> 50:54.666
"Wander number three..."

50:54.750 --> 50:56.500
No. You gotta start with Hoosier Hill.

50:56.583 --> 50:58.583
You know, you don't have to be so pushy.

50:58.666 --> 51:00.708
You say "pushy," and I hear, um...

51:01.208 --> 51:02.291
"assertive,"

51:02.750 --> 51:03.750
"bold,"

51:04.375 --> 51:05.375
"inspiring."

51:06.666 --> 51:08.791
Uh... relentless. Irritating.

51:09.291 --> 51:10.708
Arrogant.

51:11.000 --> 51:12.041
Sexy.

51:18.875 --> 51:20.666
It's nice to have a friend again.

51:27.416 --> 51:29.083
Don't let that go to your head.

51:31.458 --> 51:32.458
Too late.

51:40.416 --> 51:42.625
You know what I like about you,
Ultraviolet?

51:44.291 --> 51:45.291
What?

51:46.125 --> 51:49.708
You're all the colors in one...
at full brightness.

51:53.250 --> 51:58.416
<i>♪ Ha-ha-ha-ha ha-ha-ha-ha
Ha-ha-ha ha ♪</i>

51:59.125 --> 52:00.541
<i>♪ Ha-ah-ha ♪</i>

52:02.125 --> 52:05.250
♪ <i>Too young to burn ♪</i>

52:06.458 --> 52:09.625
<i>♪ Too young, too young ♪</i>

52:10.666 --> 52:14.041
<i>♪ Too young to burn ♪</i>

52:15.041 --> 52:19.500
<i>♪ Too young, too young ♪</i>

